sentences: Michalis Kyriakou (Greek: Μιχάλης Κυριάκου), known by his stage-name Michalis Violaris (Μιχάλης Βιολάρης) (born 9 January 1944 Agia Varvara, Nicosia Cyprus), is a popular singer and composer of modern Greek and Cypriot music.
His song "Ta Ryalia" (also "Ta Rialia") sung in Cypriot Greek became a hit in the top-10 of Greece in 1973.
In 1962 he moved to Greece where he enrolled at the school of Philosophy of Athens University and eventually obtained his degree.
His songs made Cypriot music widely popular in Greece in the 1960s and 1970s.
He won third prize at the Thessaloniki Song Festival in 1972 and in 1974 he came in second at the same festival.

In 1971 he signed with Zodiac Records, while in 1977 his records were sold under the Lyra record label.
